Enable the minigbm vc4 backend for the Raspberry Pi 4.

cros_gralloc allocates buffers through the DRM driver behind /dev/dri (vc4 on
card0). minigbm only compiles the vc4 backend when -DDRV_VC4 is set, and none
of the stock `platform` presets define it. Add it to the generic cflags so the
stock gralloc5 allocator + mapper (android.hardware.graphics.allocator-service.minigbm,
mapper.minigbm) gain vc4 support without re-declaring/vendoring them.

Apply from the AOSP top dir:  patch -p1 < device/rpi/rpi4/patches/0001-minigbm-enable-vc4-backend.patch
(or just edit the one line by hand — see below.)

--- a/external/minigbm/Android.bp
+++ b/external/minigbm/Android.bp
@@ -69,7 +69,7 @@
     srcs: ["cros_gralloc/gralloc0/gralloc0.cc"],
 }

-generic_cflags = ["-DHAS_DMABUF_SYSTEM_HEAP"]
+generic_cflags = ["-DHAS_DMABUF_SYSTEM_HEAP", "-DDRV_VC4"]
 intel_cflags = [
     "-DDRV_I915",
     "-DDRV_XE",
